    "description": "A gymnasium at Elis, described by Pausanias, now likely destroyed. Said by Pausanias to be the training grounds athletes had to pass to compete at Olympia. It included a running track called the Sacred Track, and altars to Heracles, Eros, Demeter, and a cenotaph to Achilles.",
